item.title: Virus cases mount at Woolies sites
item.description: Frustrated workers at Woolworths distribution centre in Melbourne’s southeast have been offered overtime shifts before they were told about positive coronavirus cases at the warehouses.

item.title: Man’s expensive butter chicken craving
item.description: A Melbourne man with a craving for butter chicken has been slapped with a $1652 fine after driving 32km to visit his favourite restaurant.

item.title: Murder charge over Melbourne stabbing death
item.description: A teenager has been charged with murder over the alleged stabbing death of Thomas Tran in Melbourne’s southeast in June.

item.title: Victoria records third death in 24 hours
item.description: Victoria has recorded 217 new infections, adding to the state’s total of 5353 cases.

item.title: Dogs to sniff out Vic train stowaways
item.description: Police dogs have been called in to patrol South Australian rail yards after a Melbourne group’s failed attempt to flee Victoria on a Perth-bound freight train.

item.title: NSW too ‘complacent’ as virus surges
item.description: Coronavirus cases in New South Wales have risen by 15 overnight bringing the state’s total to 3361.

item.title: Baby tragically dies in Melbourne
item.description: A 7-month-old baby has tragically died after being found unresponsive in Melbourne early on Saturday morning.

item.title: Chinese man jailed over meth barrel plot
item.description: A Chinese national has been thrown behind bars for eight years after his role in a failed attempt to smuggle liquid methamphetamine and MDMA into Australia four years ago.

item.title: Federal parliament canned over COVID
item.description: The next sitting fortnight of federal parliament has been cancelled, due to concerns of the growing coronavirus situation in Victoria and New South Wales.

item.title: Grim sign home collapse will get worse
item.description: Strong waves have caused two luxury beachfront homes along the New South Wales Central Coast to crumble overnight, and left others standing on bare metal beams.
